{"id":"clm_4930d8af41d7d7dc","text":"Ontology developers argue that coordinated, logically well-formed ontologies deliver interoperable and accurate representations of biological reality, but audits of the resulting annotations are sobering.","section":"sec-fair-preclinical","anchor":"content/04_fair_preclinical_data.md#clm_4930d8af41d7d7dc","claimType":"summary","qualification":"Source claim type: review_synthesis; modality: established; scope status: matched.","scope":{}}
{"id":"clm_4a1d41336cb3740f","text":"Even within one endpoint, a telemetry study found same-laboratory historical controls usable to detect a QTc effect but cross-laboratory controls unusable because of time-course differences between two facilities' vehicle data.","section":"sec-virtual-controls","anchor":"content/05_virtual_control_groups.md#clm_4a1d41336cb3740f","claimType":"other","qualification":"Source claim type: comparative; modality: likely; scope status: matched.","scope":{}}
