{"id":"clm_622093c3978c1027","text":"Whether a given corner of the literature is bias-free or merely under-examined is often unresolved, and the safest reading is that positivity is uninformative until publication bias has been formally tested — a step that little more than half of preclinical systematic reviews actually take.","section":"sec-repro-crisis","anchor":"content/02_reproducibility_crisis.md#clm_622093c3978c1027","claimType":"methodological","qualification":"Source claim type: methodological; modality: likely; scope status: matched.","scope":{"outcome":"publication-bias testing","method":"preclinical systematic-review practice"}}
