{"id":"clm_a300641ff2a120ed","text":"Individual meta-analyses have since put quantities on the correction: an updated review of interleukin-1 receptor antagonist in stroke found apparent efficacy of 36.2% fall to 21.9% once around thirty theoretically missing studies were imputed; a synthesis of sunitinib tumour studies calculated a 45% overestimate of effect size with not a single experiment using blinded outcome assessment; and trim-and-fill corrections have imputed 316 missing studies in chemotherapy-induced neuropathy, nineteen in stroke biomaterials, and thirteen in spinal-cord-injury nutrition, with funnel-plot asymmetry signalling the same missing-study problem in antidepressant forced-swim, ginsenoside stroke and heparin brain-injury literatures alike.","section":"sec-repro-crisis","anchor":"content/02_reproducibility_crisis.md#clm_a300641ff2a120ed","claimType":"summary","qualification":"Source claim type: review_synthesis; modality: likely; scope status: matched.","scope":{"population":"animal disease models (stroke, tumour, neuropathy, SCI, TBI)","model":"animal disease models (stroke, tumour, neuropathy, SCI, TBI)","outcome":"publication bias","method":"trim-and-fill / funnel-plot correction"}}
