{"id":"clm_a80c434c3d228a11","text":"Against this, a review of the EU endocrine-disruptor framework documents that guidance for predicting adversity with NAMs remains limited and that endocrine-disruptor identification has continued to depend on animal data, requiring further in vivo testing until alternatives are accepted.","section":"sec-nams-data","anchor":"content/06_nams_data.md#clm_a80c434c3d228a11","claimType":"other","qualification":"Source claim type: limitation; modality: likely; scope status: matched.","scope":{"outcome":"EU ED regulatory readiness","method":"NAMs for endocrine-disruptor identification"}}
