{"id":"clm_c6d69bb62fdded24","text":"Automated rigor scoring shows a slow real improvement on whole-literature indices — one index rose across two decades and scored replication studies far higher than originals — which is encouraging precisely because it is enforced at scale rather than left to authorial discretion, even though item-level manual audits in specific fields still find little movement in randomisation, blinding, and sample-size reporting.","section":"sec-governance","anchor":"content/08_governance_pathways.md#clm_c6d69bb62fdded24","claimType":"summary","qualification":"Source claim type: review_synthesis; modality: likely; scope status: minor_difference_qualified.","scope":{"population":"preclinical animal studies","model":"preclinical animal studies; automated rigor-scoring tools","outcome":"scaled enforcement vs stagnant item-level rigor","method":"ARRIVE compliance / reporting audits; automated rigor-scoring tools"}}
