{"id":"clm_dc95f68b3a930955","text":"Meanwhile the modal outcome of a research life — death — is largely omitted from the welfarist accounting that underpins the governing framework, so the animals bred to regenerate lost data are disproportionately animals killed without ever entering an analysis.","section":"sec-introduction","anchor":"content/01_introduction.md#clm_dc95f68b3a930955","claimType":"other","qualification":"Source claim type: limitation; modality: likely; scope status: minor_difference_qualified.","scope":{"population":"laboratory-animal killing/surplus death","model":"laboratory-animal killing/surplus death","outcome":"welfarist ethics and moral status of death in the 3Rs"}}
