{"id":"clm_dd70f9db8320260b","text":"This is why voluntary virtue has failed to move the field for a generation, and why an editorial mandate to declare data availability produced near-universal declarations but under one percent of trials with usable public data.","section":"sec-conclusion","anchor":"content/09_conclusion.md#clm_dd70f9db8320260b","claimType":"empirical","qualification":"Source claim type: empirical; modality: established; scope status: minor_difference_qualified.","scope":{"population":"clinical trials (JAMA/Lancet/NEJM)","model":"usable public trial data","outcome":"clinical trials (JAMA/Lancet/NEJM); voluntary vs mandated stewardship","method":"data-availability mandate vs declaration; usable public trial data"}}
